googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: This company has been absolutely wonderful! We recently bought a home and were told the tank had been pumped a year ago but the previous owners could not provide any info on when it was down or who did it. We didn’t have issues with our system but wanted to have it inspected/pumped just to make sure it was cared for. This team was able to get out to pump it 3 days after our call (it was not an emergency so I was more than happy to wait) they showed up early in the day and got the whole job completed within an hour. They showed me the tank after it was uncovered and were told it looks like it has NEVER been pumped! They were all professional and friendly, gave me advice on how to care for the tank life long as I have never had a septic tank before. They explained in great detail what to watch for and how often to have it pumped, they never tried to upsell me even though it would have been easy as I have no idea about anything septic lol they stood firm on their quote they gave me via email and were even reluctant to take a tip because they didn’t feel it was necessary. If you want an honest and friendly company that doesn’t try to milk you for money this is the one to go with! Even though they were very busy they didn’t seem inconvenienced by all of my questions 10/10 recommend

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Mr. Moore
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: I have so many good things to say about this company. From Tina (who I’ve learned is the Mom) to her son, Gage who was the guy who came to service our septic system, they were amazing. We moved into a new house a week ago and our septic stopped draining. Gage came out and pumped us and inspected the system. He confirmed it’s not draining. Gave me number to call to have new field lines drawn up then call all pro back to do the service. I have 4 sons and my toddler asks a lot of questions. Gage answered everything. He was very professional and kind. What would usually be a super stressful experience, this company is making me feel confident that it will be fine and they will handle it. Also the pricing!!!! I called 5 different septic companies to get my septic pumped and service and every quote was over 500$ to pump. Some even said it would be another 100$ to dig to be able to pump. My husband is military and dug it before he left the country. All pro came out and after military discount I was only charged 275$ for pumping and inspecting it. If you have septic issues just do yourself a favor and hire All Pro. Photo is my husband thinking he could fix the problem himself 🤣
